00:18:32,617 --> 00:18:37,719
without finding opportunities to do that while working from home or working in multiple locations.

258
00:18:38,719 --> 00:18:43,200
You miss a whole bunch of really important informal chats and

259
00:18:43,320 --> 00:18:46,480
knowledge transfer. So finding opportunities to do that as well.

260
00:18:48,382 --> 00:18:57,305
Being proactive, so making sure you actively reach out to people and ask questions and solve problems, share what's going on with you.

261
00:18:59,166 --> 00:19:03,507
Again, there's none of that kind of informal observation that we can do when we're in studio.

262
00:19:04,047 --> 00:19:11,410
So it's really important that you're reaching out when you have an issue, you're reaching out when there's something going on, or you're reaching out to ask if people have problems.

263
00:19:11,430 --> 00:19:17,352
Because you can't just like see someone frustrated in the studio, you don't see people at all.

264
00:19:19,897 --> 00:19:26,238
Setting yourself up for success, so making sure that you know when you're going to have access

265
00:19:26,278 --> 00:19:30,779
to other people. If there's multiple time zones involved it's incredibly important to think about

266
00:19:30,799 --> 00:19:36,240
this because sometimes you don't have certain people accessible. They're asleep or they're

267
00:19:36,260 --> 00:19:42,762
you know off hours and so rather than creating a culture where people feel like they need to

268
00:19:42,802 --> 00:19:47,943
be available all the time, like as if I need to be available at 4am because Fossil City started work

269
00:19:47,983 --> 00:19:48,123
then.

270
00:19:49,123 --> 00:19:54,385
We're trying to create this culture where you set yourself up for success. So people in Melbourne make

