00:20:05,609 --> 00:20:09,931
set up for tomorrow so they're not waiting around for half the day until Melbourne's come online.

274
00:20:11,651 --> 00:20:13,192
And so this is about kind of

275
00:20:14,443 --> 00:20:18,366
Having that communication when you can have it and then setting yourself up for independent work

276
00:20:18,406 --> 00:20:22,789
when you can't and making sure that during that disconnected time it's actually a positive

277
00:20:22,889 --> 00:20:26,812
because you aren't in a whole bunch of meetings you can like have a solid block to get a whole

278
00:20:26,832 --> 00:20:33,637
bunch of work done. So thinking about how you can use that time effectively. And also scheduling

279
00:20:33,657 --> 00:20:39,822
your phone notifications. Work-life balance is so important to our mental health and to avoiding

280
00:20:39,862 --> 00:20:42,904
burnout so make sure that your phone notifications aren't always on.

281
00:20:43,692 --> 00:20:48,435
While you're working from home, it is so, so easy to just start working 12-hour days

